<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Ahahaha <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomberg=
business.com/click/35377662.286337/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdz=
L2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjQtMDUtMTQvZ2FtZXN0b3Atc2hhcmVzLXN1cmdlLWFnYWluLWFzLW1lbWU=
tc3RvY2stcGhlbm9tZW5vbi1yZXR1cm5zP2NtcGlkPUJCRDA1MTQyNF9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV=
9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTI0MDUxNCZ1dG1fY=
2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB8ccd8f7f" itemprop=3D"St=
oryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000;=
 text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-=
color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">what</=
a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Meme-stock traders again piled into shares of =
GameStop Corp. and AMC Entertainment Holdings Inc. in a revival of the reta=
il-trading frenzy that had rocked markets during the pandemic.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The video-game retailer jumped as much as 113%=
 on Tuesday, while the beleaguered movie theater chain surged 129% =E2=80=
=94 triggering multiple halts in the trading of both throughout the morning=
. GameStop has picked up about $12 billion in market value this month as it=
s stock has soared, while AMC has gained some $2 billion.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The latest rally erupted on Monday following t=
he return to social media of Keith Gill, who drove the meme-stock mania of =
2021 under the moniker =E2=80=9CRoaring Kitty.=E2=80=9D Gill shot to fame t=
hat year by rallying day traders on Reddit in an effort to squeeze GameStop=
 short sellers.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On Tuesday morning, AMC announced it had compl=
eted a previously announced at-the-market offering of shares, raising about=
 $250 million in total as it sold 72.5 million shares for an average price =
of $3.45. AMC traded as high as $11.88 on Tuesday.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">So we <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbu=
siness.com/click/35377662.286337/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW=
9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjQtMDUtMTMvZ2FtZXN0b3AtaXMtYmFjaz9jbXBpZD1CQkQwNTE0MjRfT=
U9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVy=
bT0yNDA1MTQmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBcc6a9b=
b5" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-c=
olor: #ccc;">talked yesterday</a> about the GameStop rally, which appears t=
o have been sparked by Gill rather cryptically returning to Twitter/X. Gill=
 of course led GameStop=E2=80=99s January 2021 trip to the moon, and is clo=
sely associated with that company in particular. (<a href=3D"https://link.m=
ail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35377662.286337/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuaW1kYi5jb20=
vdGl0bGUvdHQxMzk1NzU2MC8/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBb1bc48ad" itemprop=3D"Sto=
ryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; =
text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-c=
olor: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">There i=
s a movie</a> about it!) But I neglected to mention that AMC =E2=80=94=C2=
=A0whose association with Gill is pretty much =E2=80=9CKeith Gill memed Gam=
eStop, and AMC was also a meme stock=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94=C2=A0rallied hard y=
esterday, apparently on pure meme-stock sympathy.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But why did AMC rally today? Well, probably al=
so meme-stock sympathy; GameStop is up again. But if I were an AMC investor=
, I suppose I would find it bullish that AMC (1) was selling a bunch of sto=
ck into the market and (2) stopped. There is a good technical reason for AM=
C investors to be happy: There is less supply coming. When AMC=E2=80=99s st=
ock rallied hard on Monday, AMC was selling into the demand. If AMC rallies=
 today, AMC will=C2=A0<em>not=C2=A0</em>be selling into the demand. It has =
finished the offering.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Which is =E2=80=A6=C2=A0bad timing? For AMC? H=
ere is <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35377662.28=
6337/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9peD9kb2M9L0FyY2hpdmVzL2VkZ2FyL2RhdGEvMDAwMT=
QxMTU3OS8wMDAxMTA0NjU5MjQwNjA4MTMvdG0yNDEyNzk5ZDJfOGsuaHRt/607f07ceef4b8524=
a319a23cB70152d11" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D=
"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-=
bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid=
; background-color: #ccc;">AMC=E2=80=99s announcement</a>; it launched a $2=
50 million=C2=A0at-the-market offering on March 28 and sold 72.5 million sh=
ares over a period of about six weeks ending yesterday. Yesterday was a rea=
lly good day for AMC! The previous six weeks, less so. My guess is that rou=
ghly one-quarter of the offering was done yesterday, to take advantage of t=
he rally.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-1" style=3D"color: #=
000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-=
bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-col=
or: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[1]</span>
</a> But that means the other three-quarters were not. The stock was tradin=
g at $8.39 at noon today, so $3.45 is not a particularly impressive price f=
or AMC to get.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I asked yesterday:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Keith Gill seems to have added like $3 billion=
 of market capitalization to GameStop by tweeting a picture of a guy. I ass=
ume he captured at most a tiny fraction of this value. Given this very part=
icular skill that he has =E2=80=94 the ability to add billions of dollars o=
f value to, at least, this stock, with essentially no effort =E2=80=94 what=
 is the best way for him to monetize it? What is the highest-value use that=
 financial markets could find for Keith Gill?</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If you were Ryan Cohen, would you hire Gill to=
 run GameStop=E2=80=99s investor relations? If you were, like, Tesla, would=
 you hire Gill to run investor relations? Trump Media &amp; Technology Grou=
p? Apple? How much would you pay him?</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Well? If you were AMC, how much would you have=
 paid=C2=A0Keith Gill to tweet a drawing of a guy leaning forward in a chai=
r=C2=A0<em>one=C2=A0</em>day into your at-the-market offering, instead of s=
ix weeks into the offering? How much would you pay Keith Gill each month fo=
r a month-ahead calendar of his social media plans?=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Also: Let=E2=80=99s say that AMC learns its le=
sson and=C2=A0<em>does=C2=A0</em>pay Gill to tweet inscrutable cartoons at =
the optimum times for its own corporate financing needs. Would=C2=A0that be=
 =E2=80=A6=C2=A0legal? Would it be market manipulation? Would it be=C2=A0<e=
m>insider trading</em>? Are Keith Gill=E2=80=99s tweets, which are maybe-so=
rt-of obliquely about GameStop, material nonpublic information=C2=A0<em>abo=
ut AMC</em>?=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Elsewhere, =E2=80=9C<a href=3D"https://link.ma=
il.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35377662.286337/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuY25iYy5jb20v=
MjAyNC8wNS8xMy9nYW1lc3RvcC1zaG9ydC1zZWxsZXJzLWhhdmUtYWxyZWFkeS1sb3N0LTEtYml=
sbGlvbi1mcm9tLW1vbmRheXMtbW9uc3Rlci1yYWxseS5odG1s/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB=
e3bba0db" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" =
style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-wi=
dth: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgro=
und-color: #ccc;">GameStop short sellers</a> lost almost $1 billion in Mond=
ay=E2=80=99s monster rally,=E2=80=9D what. <a href=3D"https://link.mail.blo=
ombergbusiness.com/click/35377662.286337/aHR0cHM6Ly9xei5jb20vbWVtZS1zdG9ja3=
MtZ2FtZXN0b3AtYW1jLXZpcmdpbi1nYWxhY3RpYy1yYWxseWluZy0xODUxNDc1ODE5/607f07ce=
