<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This was a Susquehanna interview question 25 y=
ears ago! They made me do the math on 1000 coin flips. EV(heads) (easy), st=
andard deviation (slightly harder), then they offered me a +EV bet on the o=
utcome. I said =E2=80=9Clet=E2=80=99s go.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">They said =E2=80=9CWrong. If we=E2=80=99re off=
ering it to you, you shouldn=E2=80=99t take it.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I said =E2=80=9CWe just did the math.=E2=80=9D=
</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">They said =E2=80=9CWe have a guy on the floor =
of the Amex who can flip 55% heads.=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The point here is that Susquehanna Internation=
al Group employed=C2=A0a guy who was really good at flipping coins so they =
land heads,=C2=A0<em>so that=C2=A0</em>Susquehanna=E2=80=99s traders didn=
=E2=80=99t get too cocky about their bets. =E2=80=9CI=E2=80=99ve done the m=
ath and this trade has positive expected value,=E2=80=9D they will say, but=
 then they=E2=80=99ll pause and remember the coin-flip guy and think =E2=80=
=9Cif this trade really has positive expected value, why is it being offere=
d to me,=E2=80=9D and they think a bit harder about it and become better tr=
aders.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This lesson applies beyond individual trades. =
For instance, there is the structure of the investment management industry.=
 Agustin Lebron, a former Jane Street trader, has a very good book called=
