olor: #ccc;"><em>The Laws of Trading</em></a>, in which he says:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The profitable trades that exist i=
n the world are either (a) the ones you=E2=80=99re intimately involved in r=
unning, or (b) the ones that are inaccessible to you. There is no (c). And =
what=E2=80=99s funny about the situation in trading is that, if we were tal=
king about just about any other industry, the very notion of a (c) would be=
