yle: solid; background-color: #ccc;">the old Hemingway line</a>: =E2=80=9CH=
ow did _____ go bankrupt? Two ways. Gradually, then suddenly.=E2=80=9D<a cl=
ass=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-3" style=3D"color: #000000; text-d=
ecoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: =
#000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transparen=
t !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[3]</span>
</a>=C2=A0Hemingway says it about a person, and personal bankruptcy doesn=
=E2=80=99t <em>have </em>to happen that way: People can go bankrupt suddenl=
y and then gradually (medical debt), or only gradually (overspending), or o=
nly suddenly (casino). Even <em>business </em>bankruptcy sometimes involves=
 a slow steady slide into insolvency; we <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloom=
bergbusiness.com/click/35377662.286337/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9v=
cGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjQtMDUtMDkvYmVkLWJhdGgtc3RyaWtlcy1mcm9tLXRoZS1iZXl=
